snippet.textDisplay: The foolproof eggdrop contest entry is putting an egg in a glass jar, filling the jar with pancake syrup, closing the jar, putting that jar in a larger glass jar, filling the rest of that one with syrup, and closing it. It always wins. The outer jar will break and you'll have to clean up syrup everywhere, but the egg never breaks at least. The effect is an egg within another egg within another egg.
snippet.textOriginal: The foolproof eggdrop contest entry is putting an egg in a glass jar, filling the jar with pancake syrup, closing the jar, putting that jar in a larger glass jar, filling the rest of that one with syrup, and closing it.
